  <h1 class="gd-h1">Iceland vs the World</h1>
  <p class="gd-lede">British Columbia, Alaska, Japan, the Alps — the world's great heliski regions each hold a genuine claim to greatness, and none of them is wrong. This chapter sets Iceland fairly beside them, praising what each does best, and then shows precisely where the Troll Peninsula's sea-to-summit skiing carves out a place all its own. If you would rather start with the practicalities, browse <a href="/packages">the packages</a>.</p>
